Both male and women graduates of prestigious universities, as opposed to others with less education, consider abortion to be indifferent in terms of their choice of a sexual partner. Men’s educational status does not seem to matter in this instance.

The majority of men in both Serbia and the Northern Serbian region believe that there is an unacceptable level of sexual harassment in private and public spheres in Serbia in general, and the Northern Serbian region in particular.

The research findings suggest that men in the Northern Serbian region feel a bit threatened by the feminist wave in Serbia regardless of their political beliefs. Moreover, transgressive discourse among feminist activists represents a new and threatening lifestyle both for men and women and challenges the status quo in terms of socio-demographic context and culture. Hence, the essentialist identity similar to that which exists within the historical patriarchal mechanisms that structural or repressive institutions use does not allow space for freedom of choice in today’s feminism. Hence, the gender essentialist and gendered notions that belie the feminist movement have the potential of neutralizing the anti-globalist potential of cultural gymnastics and gain transgressive sexual identity.
